{
  "stem": "13313.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 14.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "From home, I picked up Yiddish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then after the war, I-- when in Canada, when I went to university, I also took up some pretty advanced Spanish as well.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "These are-- at one time, I knew these thoroughly, these languages.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And than a few others that I just have a smattering of.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "A little bit of Polish because my parents were speaking Polish to each other, so we should understand what was going on, and I picked some up from that, yes.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "All right.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- some of the interesting parts were that the-- the-- the difference between the two sets of instructions, the two cultures.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, the Hebrew teachers were pretty-- teaching by rote-- very strict people.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the other side was a little bit more lax.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Interesting that happened was that school actually stayed open until 1942.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the Germans occupied Belgium, I believe, on May 10, 1940.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That's when they invaded.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And as a result, they-- once they got organized, the school was still running, but they dismissed the Hebrew people, and they replaced them with a-- a pro-- a pro-German principal.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And some of the Flemish Gentile teachers were, in a way, collaborators with the occupying troops, forces, and started to appear in brown shirts, kind of SS uniforms.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they were very, very rough on the Jewish children.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "This was part of the-- that lasted only till the summer of '42 because summer of '42, that's when the Germans, after a lot of-- imposed a lot of restrictions on the community, isolating them, and identifying them, and with some-- and-- and with a lot of the things which we'll come to, perhaps, later.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They finally then decided this-- this was the time to start deporting and-- and-- and destroying the community.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
